description: {"blocks":[{"key":"cmo5d","text":"This protocol outlines a cost-effective approach for amplicon sequencing of P. falciparum malaria from dried blood spots (DBS). The protocol can be conducted in ~2-3 days and costs ~USD $25/sample. We currently have two target panels, NOMADS8 and NOMADS16, which were developed using multiply (https://github.com/JasonAHendry/multiply). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":76,"length":13}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":294,"length":40}],"data":{}},{"key":"30r1o","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ptab","text":"Here, we describe how to generate the primer pools and prepare the library for sequencing. The protocol starts from dried-blood spot (DBS) extracted DNA. To date, most of our tests have been with samples extracted using Qiagen QIAamp kits (see Materials) and we observe good performance for samples with parasitemia \u003e 1000p/uL. The assay performs better on fresher samples compared to those that have spent a long time as DBS. It is advisable to include positive controls in your experiment (for example, lab strains mixed with human DNA to mimic DBS-extracted DNA) as well as non-template controls.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bhud3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"968m8","text":"We welcome your questions and/or feedback on the protocol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"CC4EAAB9A62411EDA02B0A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://github.com/JasonAHendry/multiply"}}}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"a29jf","text":"To each sample, add 0.5uL of the assigned native barcode.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6hiu2","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1chmu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"fq82f","text":"This step requires attention; double check your tips to ensure that 0.5uL of barcode is being delivered to every sample. steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"34u72","text":"Add 6.2uL of the barcode ligation master mix to each sample, mix well by pipetting and spin down.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"94co8","text":"Return the plate to the thermal cycler and press “Enter” to move the program through: 20°C for 20 mins -\u003e 65°C for 10mins -\u003e 8°C forever.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"f73d8","text":"Pool equal volumes of each sample to a LoBind 1.5mL Eppendorf Tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cr6pg","text":"Perform a 0.4X ratio SPRI bead clean-up.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"82o8j","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"256o4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":19,"offset":27,"style":"bold"}],"key":"46rbp","text":"Ensure your SPRI beads are at room temperature!","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":15,"offset":23,"style":"bold"}],"key":"22rp8","text":"Vortex your SPRI beads for 30s or more to ensure they are in suspension before pipetting!","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":27,"offset":10,"style":"italic"}],"key":"15v2b","text":"Prepare a fresh stock of 80% ethanol each time.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fb7a1","text":"To the pooled DNA, add SPRI beads at a 0.4X ratio.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d7cj6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"668ve","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"anq09","text":"For example, if your pool is 100uL add 40uL of SPRI beads.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2bjh9","text":"Mix thoroughly by pipetting or vortexing. Ensure the beads are mixed visually. If vortexing, spin down but do not pellet beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":42,"length":35}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"bqr7a","text":"Incubate for 5 mins at RT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9dbkr","text":"Incubate on the magnet for 8 mins.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"eu2su","text":"Remove the supernatant. Do not transfer any beads, if this is a risk leave ~5uL of supernatant behnid with the beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8cl5g","text":"Wash the beads with 80% ethanol. Leave for 30 secs. Ensure the ethanol complete covers the pelleted beads – use an amount greater than the amount of sample + beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ad9cn","text":"Remove and discard supernatant. Repeat ethanol wash.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2s6fm","text":"Spin down the samples, place back on the magent and remove any residual ethanol. Ensure all ethanol is removed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":81,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"72lr4","text":"Air dry the beads until they look dry, e.g. ~30s.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"joth","text":"Resuspend the beads in 70uL nuclease-free water by pipetting.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b4dca","text":"Wait 2 to 5 mins while DNA is released from the beads. Wait longer for longer DNA fragments.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4s4nr","text":"Return samples to the magnet for 2 mins or until beads have pelleted and the solution is clear.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"abbgn","text":"Transfer 67uL of supernatant to a clean plate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4sr14","text":"QC  2uL of the cleaned pool using the Qubit.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Sample pooling and SPRI bead clean-up.
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7tt4j","text":"Aim to pass 1 to 2ug (1000 to 2000ng) of pooled DNA into the adapter ligation reaction, making up to 65uL in nuclease-free water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
